Source: tlp
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Thomas Koch <linrunner@gmx.net>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7)
Standards-Version: 3.8.4
Homepage: http://thinkpad-wiki.org/TLP_-_Stromspareinstellungen_fuer_Ubuntu

Package: tlp
Architecture: all
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, pm-utils
Recommends: ethtool, wireless-tools
Suggests: smartmontools
Conflicts: pm-utils-powersave-policy
Description: Saves battery power on laptops
 TLP is a collection of scripts enabling laptop-mode and
 implementing power save features for laptop hardware.
 Settings include harddisk advanced power management, sata aggressive 
 link power management, wifi power saving, sound power saving,
 usb autosuspend, phc controls aka "undervolting" (requires kernel 
 support) and battery charge thresholds (ThinkPads only). 
 Optical drives can be powered off on battery (ThinkPad
 Ultrabay devices only). Wifi, bluetooth and wwan devices 
 can be selectively disabled on system startup and shutdown.
